reviewText: This was another event I saw courtesy of WCW 24/7 and this was a memorable events for various reasons. This PPV was hosted by Johnny B. Badd, Missy Hyatt, and Eric Bischoff while Jim Ross & Jesse Ventura did the commentary. Maxx Payne also performed the National Anthem on his gutair. The big story here was the return of Ric Flair to WCW after his run in WWF...which also marked the first time Ric Flair & Jesse Ventura had interacted on television.Brian Pillman & Steve Austin vs. Erik Watts & Marcus Alexander Bagwell - This marked the PPV debut of the tag team that would go on to be known as the "Hollywood Blondes." Austin & Pillman gave Erik Watts the best match in his career here as they gave a great opening tag team match. It's nothing memorable but compared to most of the matches on the card, this was the "sleeper" bout.2 Cold Scorpio vs. Chris Benoit - Scorpio's style was unique & very underrated in WCW at this time while Benoit was in his early stages of his career at this time as well. The match was a 20 min. time limit & they wrestled all the way to 1 sec. short of the time limit. This was a wrestling masterpiece for that day & age in WCW eventhough they would go on to better boughts in ECW.(Also available on "Hard Knocks: The Chris Benoit Story")Davey Boy Smith vs. Bill Irwin - Memorable moment #3 here as the British Bulldog makes his WCW debut here in a quick squash match. The post-match promo which Davey stuttered & stumbled over his own words was more interesting than this match.Falls Count Anywhere Match: Cactus Jack vs. Paul Orndorff - Cactus just turned babyface around a month earlier and you saw that aggression & intensity from Orndorff that you haven't seen since his fued with Hogan back in '86. Cactus busted up Orndorff's pre-match interview and they fought all over the ringside area including using weapons such as a knee brace & even a shovel. This was a wild brawl that was actually the match of the night for me.Rock N' Roll Express vs. Heavily Bodies - This formation of the Heavily Bodies consisted of Tom Prichard & Stan Lane with Bobby Eaton & Jim Cornette as ringside before Eaton got thrownout of ringside. This was an average tag match was the Express were out of their prime at this time while the Bodies were just a last min. replacement for the recently released Wrecking Crew. This match didn't do anything for me.WCW United States Champion Dustin Rhodes vs. Maxx Payne - Dustin Rhodes' original opponett was suppost to be Ron Simmons but he was injured so Payne took his place. Payne just isn't a good wrestler & while Dustin is a natural in the ring (hense his nickname "The Natural"), this match wasn't watchable as Dustin couldn't carry Payne & the ending of Payne getting disqualified didn't help either.NWA Champion Great Muta vs. Barry Windham - Flair came to ringside to call this match. Windham's ground game actually meshed well with Muta's japanese style here in a very underrated match in WCW's history. It ended with Windham finally reaching the potental people saw in him years upon years earlier as he finally became a World Champion...with Ric Flair actually putting the belt (that he never lost) around Windham's waist.Strap Match: Sting vs. Vader - Despite the corny "White Castle Of Fear" storyline (which parts of the vigenettes were shown thoughout the time), this was a stiff strap match. And I say the match was stiff as Vader got hit so hard various times that his back was heavily bleeding thoughout the bout. The match itself was probably not as good as the other Sting/Vader match I've seen (Starrcade 92) as it was slow at times with the "touch the four corners" concept of a strap match. The ending was the sterotypical ending to a strap match where the winner won by accident as Sting pushed Vader into the final turnbuckle.Overall, this was just an average WCW PPV with good matches but nothing that sticks out in your mind or is memorable plus the Benoit/Scorpio match is available on DVD (without Ventura's commentary). This is one event that I recommend at a low price.

reviewText: This is a very well done WCW show!  SuperBrawl III saw the return of Ric Flair to WCW, the debut of the British Bulldog, Barry Windham vs. the Great Muta for the NWA World Heavyweight title, a classic bout between Chris  Benoit and 2 Cold Scorpio, and a brutal leather strap match between Sting  and WCW World Champion Big Van Vader.  In addition, Cactus Jack takes on  Paul Orndorff in a falls count anywhere match!  Great show

reviewText: Superbrawl III is an over looked Pay Per View cause of the year it took place in 1993 it's not a well liked year but I personally enjoyed 1993. So I'm going to fill in some of the backstory for this show. 1st off Bill Watts left WCW & Eric Bischoff took his place. He took Jim Ross off of TV Jim Ross left WCW & went to The WWF. Now WCW was trying to get Ric Flair back with the company. Flair had left The WWF in January so he started negotating with Watts before he left. On December 30th at a House Show Vader defeated Ron Simmons for The WCW World Heavyeight  Championship. He also wanted to have some kind of match with Sting. At Clash Of The Champions 22 Vader cut a promo about The White Castle of Fear strap match. But you had  aThunderdome cage match at this Clash with Sting, Dustin Rhodes, Ron Simmons & Van Hamer vs Vader, Rick Rude, Barry Windham & The Barbarian, Now there were a lot of injuries going on Rick Rude couldn't compete casue of his neck injury. Van Hammer had a muscle tear. Harley Race decided to have a Paul Orndorff wrestle Cactus Jack for Rude's spot. On The January 10th episode of The Main Event Race turned on Cactus Jack Ordorff won later on in the show Cactus Jack attacked Race, Vader & Ordorff with a shovel. During The Clash Of Champions 22 Vader, Windham & Ordorff laid The Barbarian out. Vader was interviewed during the show Ron Simmons came out & confornted him where Vader attacked him & hurt his already injured shoulder so Simmons was out of the match. During The Thunderdome Cage Match Cactus Jack came down to help Sting & Dustin Rhodes to get the win.  On The January 30th  episode of WCW Saturday Night they brought back those wonderful mini movies where Sting took a helicopeter to The Rocky Mountains to face Vader in The White Castle Of Fear where they had a tug of war & it said to be continued at Superbrawl III. On this episode Sting & Dustin Rhodes teamed up to face Vader & Barry Windham they were distqaulified Vader & Windham whipped Sting with the strap. On The January 30th episode of World Wide Vader used the strap to hang Sting. On The Febuary 6th episode of WCW Saturday Nigth Sting took on Barry Windham he sent a message to Vader he took the strap that Windham had brought with him & hung him over the ropes. Vader was sencing his own messages to Sting where after he destroyed a jobber Harley Race would paint there face like Sting Vader would take the strap & whip them. On The February 20th episode of WCW Saturday Night Sting said I'm going into this match with all the people Vader has hurt on his mind.On The January 23rd episode of WCW Saturday Night Barry Windham got a shot at The NWA World Heavyweight Championship at Superbrawl III The Great Muta won The NWA World Championship at on January 4th  in Tokyo at Fantastic Story In Tokyo. when he beat Masahiro Chono. On The Febuary 20th episode of WCW Saturday Night Gordon Solie interviewed Barry Windham he mentioned the men that have been The NWA World Champion. Windham said he isn't here to talk about the past especially Flair  he's here to talk about The Great Muta. Windham said that I will take it to the ragged edge if I have to.  Now back to The Cactus Jack situation on The January 16th episode of WCW Saturday Nigth Cactus Jack took on Paul Orndorff Vader interfered & cost Cactus Jack the match he also attacked him after the match. Cactus Jack proised that he would go after Vader soon but 1st he would take on Paul Orndorff in a no disqualification match at Superbrawl III. Rick Rude failed to meet the date to defend The US Championship so on The January 16th episode of WCW Saturday Night Dustin Rhodes defeated Ricky Steamboat in the finals of The US title tournamet Barry Windham came down & DDT'd Steamboat the concrete. Steamboat failed to make it to the ring. On The Febuary 13th episode of WCW Saturday Night it was announced that Dustin Rhodes would defend The US title against Ron Simmons at Superbrawl. Jim Cornette, Stan Lane & Tom Pritchard showed up on this episode & frm what I have heard is that Bischoff had a lot of the stuff Cornette was saying cut out. Cause Bischoff didn't want to work with S M  W. On The January 2nd episode of WCW Saturday Night The Hollywood Blonds formed cause Barry Windham told Brian Pillman that he is focusing on his singles run he gave him Steve Austin as a tag team partner. At The Clash Of Champions 22 Pillman & Austin faced Ricky Steamboat & Shane Douglas for The NWA & WCW World Tag Team Championship. It ended in a disqaulification Douglas was cut open. Also Erik Watts & Arn Anderosn were involved in a fight in a parking lot where Watts was arrested cause Bill Watts was pushing his son still This covers The backstory I hope. The buyrate was a 0.50 that is down from last years 0.96.February 21, 1993Attendance 6,500Venue Asheville Civic CenterCity Asheville, North Carolina1st thing Eric Bischoff announces that Ron Simmons is injured & can't compete. So newcommer Max Payne takes his place.The Hollywood Blonds Steve Austin & Brian Pillman Def Erik Watts & Marcus Alexander Bagwell ***Erik Watts is booed badly. I don't blame the fans for giving him so much s  h  i  t.Bischoff & Johnny Badd are talking about Ric Flair's return to WCW while Missy Hyatt is in the back trying to interview Ric Flair but his security won't let her. Flair comes out of the limo & WOOOO!2 Cold Scorpio Def he who we will not speak of aka  Chris Benoit *** & 3 quarters of a star.Eric Bischoff interviewed Max Payne he plays t a  p  s on his guitar for Dustin RhodesThe British Bulldog Def Wild Bill Irwin *Tony Schiavone interviewed him after the match The Bulldog says he wants to challenge for The WCW World title.Cactus Jack interrupts Paul Orndorff's interview he attacked him with a shovel which goes into this next matchNO DQ falls count anywhereCactus Jack Def Paul Ordorff ** & a half stars decent fightThe Rock N Roll Express Richard Morton & Robert Gibson Def The Heavenly Bodies Stan Lan & Tom Pritchard with Jim Cornette ** & half stars decent match Cornette was funny in this match too.WCW United States ChampionshipChampion Dustin Rhodes Def Max Payne by disqualification * & 3 quarters of a star Payne hit the ref on purposeRic Flair came out to do commentary with Schiavone & Ventura he got the loudest reaction of the night. He said he's here to watch the match for a title that he never lost. .NWA World Heavyweight ChampionshipBarry Windham Def Champion The Great Muta **** & a quarter of a star Windham got a nice pop from the crowd when he won. During the match Flair was talking about what if Muta loses Ventura says "No Shushi for him for a year." Flair came in & put the belt on Windham & Windham's reaction is priceless. I can't say that this is a forgotten classic but it is a great match that is forgottenLeather Strap Matchnon titleVader Def Sting **** & half starsThis was another great match by these 2. This match I forgot how brutal it was especially for early to mid 90's. Only other promotion that would do brutal matchs was ECW. But they did brutal matches all the time.This Pay Per View is amazing & probably over looked  but I recommend it it has something for everybody. My next wrestling review will be The 1st Slamboree.
summary: The Nature Boy comes back home WOOOO! 9.5/10

reviewText: Superball 3 was sloppy as h$ll, but its still classic WCW so it's expected.  The White Castle of fear main event is pretty good, but the PPV intro of it is not...let me explain.  Sting bursts into this production set of "the white castle" which looks like umm well a castle inwhich we are lead to believe Vader lives, and where Sting has come to accept the challenge in Vader's White Castle of fear.  Some lame jokes are exchanged worst being Stings attempt at comedy and teh the thing blows up and the PPV begin's, which is sponsered by...White Castle hamburgers, how pathetic.  Also every wrestler looks as thow they've had there luggage stolen and are wearing some of the worst ring attire ever produced.  Vader flaunts a animal skin cape to the ring to give you an idea.  But still its worth it.
summary: WCW CLASIC GARBAGE THAT YOU JUST GOTTA LOVE
